  "tool_calls": [
    {
      "name": "Skill",
      "args": {
        "skill": "stm32debug",
        "args": "Take a debug snapshot of the attached target."
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "Bash",
      "args": {
        "command": "stm32 debug snapshot",
        "description": "Take a composite debug snapshot (registers + callstack + disasm-around-PC) of the attached target"
      }
    }
  ],
  "final_text": "\"Take a debug snapshot\" maps directly to `stm32 debug snapshot`. ELF autodiscovery will pick it up from the project descriptor if present.\nThe snapshot failed \u2014 the ST-LINK firmware on the attached probe is out of date. The gdbserver exited with code 6 and reported:\n\n> **ST-LINK firmware upgrade required. Please upgrade the ST-LINK firmware using the upgrade tool.**\n\n**What to do:**\n\n1. Open **STM32CubeProgrammer** \u2192 menu **Firmware Upgrade** (or run `STM32_Programmer_CLI --upgrade` from the command line).\n2. Select the detected ST-LINK probe and click **Upgrade**.\n3. Once the upgrade completes, re-plug the USB cable (or power-cycle the board).\n4. Re-run the snapshot:\n   ```\n   stm32 debug snapshot\n   ```\n\nThis is the same ST-LINK V2J28M17 firmware issue noted for the bench F401RE board \u2014 the fix is the same firmware upgrade path."
}